    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the CFD model meets MRL 2 requirements for 11 of 13 factors at or above required levels. The shortfall in Relevance of Validation Activities to COU (achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) was acknowledged but not treated as disqualifying on the grounds that steady-state conditions were argued to represent a conservative bound on worst-case shear exposure. No pulsatile experimental comparator was identified or linked. The primary hemolysis validation result does not carry a comparedAgainst reference to any experimental dataset. The assessment team accepted these gaps under the judgment that the overall evidence body, taken together, provides sufficient confidence for a Class II device at MRL 2. The decision is recorded as Accepted with the recommendation that pulsatile validation be conducted prior to any MRL 3 submission.",
